    <h4 id="qwer-config-js"><a href="#qwer-config-js">QWER.config.js</a></h4>
    <p><strong>Generally, you do NOT need to modify this file at all.</strong></p>
    <p>
      QWER comes with image pre-process procedure. It will take your cover image or other image assets that are
      referenced in the post, and generate smaller resoultions and image formats that has better compression while
      maintaining similar visual quality.
    </p>
